.TH "drm_mode_object_add" 9 "drm_mode_object_add" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_mode_object_add \- allocate a new modeset identifier
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drm_mode_object_add
.BI "(struct drm_device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct drm_mode_object *obj "  ","
.BI "uint32_t obj_type "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
DRM device
.IP "obj" 12
object pointer, used to generate unique ID
.IP "obj_type" 12
object type
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Create a unique identifier based on \fIptr\fP in \fIdev\fP's identifier space.  Used
for tracking modes, CRTCs and connectors.
.SH "RETURN"
Zero on success, error code on failure.
